hidden_size = 512

ðŸ§  B. Use nn.BCEWithLogitsLoss() instead of Sigmoid + BCELoss:
 Replace final Sigmoid layer in D:
nn.Linear(hidden_size, 1)  # No Sigmoid
# Replace loss function:
criterion = nn.BCEWithLogitsLoss()

ðŸš€ A. Normalize real/fake labels with noise:
real_labels = torch.ones(images.size(0), 1).uniform_(0.8, 1.0).to(device)
fake_labels = torch.zeros(images.size(0), 1).uniform_(0.0, 0.2).to(device)

ðŸ§Š B. Use weight initialization:
def weights_init(m):
    if isinstance(m, nn.Linear):
        nn.init.xavier_uniform_(m.weight)
        if m.bias is not None:
            nn.init.zeros_(m.bias)

D.apply(weights_init)
G.apply(weights_init)

âœ… 5. GAN-Specific Improvements
ðŸŽ› A. Try using convolutional GAN (DCGAN):
Your model is fully connected, which is not ideal for image data. Try nn.Conv2d-based D and nn.ConvTranspose2d-based G when you're comfortable.


âœ… 6. Monitoring & Debugging Tips
plt.plot(d_losses, label='D Loss')
plt.plot(g_losses, label='G Loss')
plt.legend()
plt.title("Losses")
plt.show()


